spans.text: of yore To the swift-winged Hermes bore
like thy sire thou lovest to seem Light and gay with pinions trim
Light and gay with pinions trim
like thy mother drear and sad , ( All in mournful vestments clad , Cypress weeds and sable stole , ) Thou rushest on the affrighted soul
her noon , And darkness , partner of her reign , Round the world hath bound her chain
the night hath reached her noon , And darkness , partner of her reign , Round the world hath bound her chain
Sudden I stop , and turn my ear , And listening
thee I rove Bosomed in the sheltering grove , There , with heart and lyre new strung , Meditate the lofty song
Bosomed in the sheltering grove , There , with heart and lyre new strung , Meditate the lofty song
some moral page My attentive thoughts engage
ages long past over , When Truth and Virtue hand in hand Walked upon the smiling land
Wild music wandering in the air
that famed clue , Which led the Athenian's unskilled feet Through the Labyrinth of Crete
the Athenian's unskilled feet Through the Labyrinth of Crete
if thou with magic wand On my temples take thy stand
All that struck my waking eyes
the vast desert of the sky
holds its mirror to the sun
